description.narrative: As part of a regionally-managed water resources project, selected river-basin management organizations on both sides of cross-border rivers and water basins will receive assistance for the preparation of their own annual basin management plans. Water basin organization members receive training and technical assistance as they move through the plan in order to learn how to conduct it step by step. Coordinated management of shared water resources is fostered between basin-management organizations on both sides of the cross-boundary rivers and water basins.

Objectives for Kyrgyzstan: EXPECTED RESULTS AND ACHIEVEMENTS: Water managers in Central Asia and Afghanistan understand and apply sustainable IWRM on policy and applied levels. Networking, collaboration and trust among future water managers across Central Asia and Afghanistan have increased. National water ministries apply IWRM principles and provide improved support to Basin Management Organization. Basin planning principles in selected basins have improved.
